Package gov.nih.nlm.ling.sem

Class ImplicitRelation

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nih.nlm.ling.sem.AbstractRelation
      • gov.nih.nlm.ling.sem.ImplicitRelation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Relation, SemanticItem, java.lang.Comparable<SemanticItem>

    public class ImplicitRelation
extends AbstractRelation
    Implementation of a relation that is implicit; in other words, there are no predicates that indicate the relation. Implicit discourse relations between sentences is one example of such relations.
    Author:
    Halil Kilicoglu

      • toStandoffAnnotation

        public java.lang.String toStandoffAnnotation​()
        Gets the standoff annotation text for the implicit relation.

        The standoff annotation format for an implicit relation is the following (tab after [ID]) [ID] [TYPE] [ARG1_ROLE]:[ARG1_ID] [ARG2_ROLE]:[ARG2:ID] ...

        Returns:
        the string representation in standoff annotation format
